DIANA MFG. CO. v. INTERNATIONAL CELLUCOTTON PRODUCTS COMPANY. No. 5112. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Dec. 6, 1933. C. A. Soans, of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, SPARKS, and FITZHENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed that this cause be docketed in this court, and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed; any costs in the Court of Appeals in connection therewith to be paid by appellant.
